    - "Theme: __trunc__/__round__/__index__ dict-presence (math.trunc(x), round(x), operator.index(x))."
    - "All values False — UUID, Struct, and socket types have no truncation, rounding, or integer-conversion protocol."
    - "uuid.UUID is a Python-level class; it does not define __trunc__, __round__, or __index__ in its __dict__."
    - "uuid.UUID instances are immutable identity objects — they do not support math.trunc(x), round(x), or operator.index(x)."
    - "All values are False — uuid.UUID has no truncation, rounding, or integer-conversion protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across uuid.UUID."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
